wscape\n|\nWe sinned for no reason but an incomprehensible lack of love, and He saved us for no reason but an incomprehensible excess of love.\n\n- Peter Kreeft, Jesus-Shock\n|\nYou can't always be right, but you can be wrong a lot less\n\n- Benny Bellamacina, Philosophical Uplifting Quotes and Poems\n|\nI'd sell my soul to have you. In my whole life, you'll always be what I wanted most.'~ Hardy Cates\n\n- Lisa Kleypas, Sugar Daddy\n|\nWhen you betray someone, First you betray to yourself who speak somewhere inside you that you are good human\n\n- Mohammed Zaki Ansari, 'Zaki's Gift Of Love'\n|\nI know in my heart that man is good, that what is right will always eventually triumph, and there is purpose and worth to each and every life.\n\n- Ronald\n|\nAnd yet,to say the truth, reason and love keep little company together nowadays.\n\n- William Shakespeare, A Midsummer Night's Dream\n|\nIf you find yourself drawn to an event against all logic, go. The universe is telling you something.\n\n- Gloria Steinem, My Life on the Road\n|\nBy Aladdin's lamplit scrotum, man! Everything is a story. What is there but stories? Stories are the only truth.\n\n- Christopher Moore, Practical Demonkeeping\n|\nIf I knew how and where to sacrifice myself, I must know how and where to save myself.\n\n- Melita Tessy, Battle of the Spheres: Crust, Mantle and Core\n|\nLife is a piece of art drawn by love on the canvas of hope with the colors of desires, wants, and needs.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nThose who want to buy wisdom remain with out wisdom, because money buys nothing except commodities.\n\n- Meseret\n|\nIf you have nothing in common with the person you are dating and his parents hate you and your friends hate him, this is not romantic; it's a bad idea.\n\n- Amy E. Spiegel, Letting Go of Perfect: Women, Expectations, and Authenticity\n|\nThe truth will set you free, they say, but believe me, nothing will set you free.\n\n- Ava Farmehri, Through the Sad Wood Our Corpses Will Hang\n|\nMake no mistake, those who write long books have nothing to say.Of course those who write short books have even less to say.\n\n- Mark Z. Danielewski, House of Leaves\n|\nI wonder how it takes you, that moment when everything turns to shadows. - Somerled.\n\n- Juliet Marillier, Wolfskin"